description: The fresh Office for National Statistics figures provided the first statistical evidence that poor health prompted by the pandemic may be causing Britain's labour market squeeze.

title: CRAIG BROWN: Houston, the space buffet has a problem
description: CRAIG BROWN: January: Buckingham Palace announces that, so as to prevent further misunderstandings during encounters with the public,  the Royal Family will be fitted with headcams.

title: Oxford University chief paid for 'best education' possible for her children at private school
description: The revelation from state-educated Professor Dame Louise Richardson, 64, comes amid the ongoing row about taxing fees.

title: Neighbors of Fame star Irene Cara say she became a hermit during her final years living in Florida
description: Academy Award-winning singer and actress Irene Cara, 63, was found dead inside her Largo, Florida last month. Neighbors say the Flashdance singer and Fame actor was a recluse and was rarely seen.

title: Ex-bikie Moudi Tajjour issues ominous warning to his Mongol enemies after Bunnings bashing
description: A former Nomads bikie and convicted killer who was allegedly savagely bashed in a Bunnings car park has walked back his threats about the attack and tried to joke about the humiliating incident.

title: The View descends into farce as token conservative claims the show is full of 'toxic femininity'
description: Alyssa Farah Griffin was interrupted by her co-host on The View, Ana Navarro, while discussing 'toxic femininity'. Griffin, who worked in the Trump White House, said the show was not supportive of its hosts.

title: Spilt Milk meningococcal death: Girl, 18, dies from infection after attending Canberra festival
description: An 18-year-old girl has died from a meningococcal infection after attending one of Australia's most popular music festivals with her heartbroken family turning off life support on Sunday.

title: Anthony Albanese breaks silence over Covid diagnosis
description: The Prime Minister was forced to delay the face-to-face talks at a dinner with leaders at Kirribilli House after he tested positive following a routine PCR test on Monday.

title: Australian tourist allegedly raped in Bali after meeting Nigerian man at Kuta bar
description: An Australian woman's blissful Bali holiday has turned into a nightmare after she was allegedly sexually assaulted by a fellow tourist in Kuta after he whisked her away on his scooter on Friday.

title: Banks were 'banned' from making credit checks on Covid loan applicants during pandemic, MPs hear
description: Bosses of major lenders said it was 'incredible' they were not allowed to run usual credit or affordability checks on applicants to the Government's emergency Bounce Back Loan scheme.

title: Daniel Andrews internet trolls attack his daughter after the Victoria Premier posts photo
description: Internet trolls have taunted Daniel Andrews and his daughter Grace Andrews after the Victoria premier shared a photo of her on social media.

title: Robbie Williams 'risks the wrath of his neighbour Jimmy Page by submitting plans to erect £2m fence'
description: The singer, 48, is said to have submitted an application to Kensington and Chelsea council to put up the wooden trellis on three sides of the property.

title: Migrant who died after contracting diphtheria had been discharged from hospital, inquest hears
description: Husean Hseb, 31, said to be a Kurd, suffered multiple organ failure after he was returned to hospital on November 19 with a fever.

title: John Bolton is considering running for president in 2024 just to stop Trump
description: John Bolton threatened to jump in the 2024 presidential race if other Republicans don't step up and condemn former President Donald Trump's attack on the Constitution.

title: Father Mick Reynolds mourns son Lockie before learning boy wasn't his after $110k in child support
description: Mick Reynolds, 43, learnt the devastating truth two years after Lockie Hernaman died of an unexplained heart condition during footy training in Harvey, south of Perth in 2019

title: EDEN CONFIDENTIAL: Kate wears earrings by designer who started business with Prince's Trust loan
description: EDEN CONFIDENTIAL: I can reveal that Catherine wore a pair of earrings during her visit to the USA with Prince William last week that were created by Londoner Lenique Louis.

title: Shark sighting at Bondi Beach, Sydney: Two hammerheads seen inside the nets of Australian beach
description: Two hammerhead sharks were spotted swimming just off the coast of one of Australia's most popular beaches, inside the nets that are supposed to keep them out.
